import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { IonButton, IonButtons, IonCard, IonCardContent, IonCardHeader, IonCol, IonContent, IonGrid, IonHeader, IonImg, IonInput, IonItem, IonItemDivider, IonList, IonPage, IonRow, IonTitle, IonToolbar } from '@ionic/react';
import ExploreContainer from '../components/ExploreContainer';
import './Tab2.css';
import { RouteComponentProps } from 'react-router';

const Tab2: React.FC<RouteComponentProps> = (props) => {
  
  const [text, setText] = useState<string>();

  return (
    <IonPage>
      <IonHeader>
        <IonToolbar>
          <IonTitle>Explore</IonTitle>
        </IonToolbar>
      </IonHeader>
      <IonContent fullscreen>
        <IonItemDivider>
          <IonInput value={text} placeholder="Search Clubs" onIonChange={e => setText(e.detail.value!)}></IonInput>
          <IonButton>Filter</IonButton>
        </IonItemDivider>
        <IonGrid>
          <IonCol>
            <IonCard button>
              <IonImg src="dunno"></IonImg>
              <IonCardHeader>Club Name</IonCardHeader>
              <IonCardContent>Quick description of the club</IonCardContent>
              <IonList>
                <IonItem>Tag 1</IonItem>
                <IonItem>Tag 2</IonItem>
              </IonList>
            </IonCard>
          </IonCol>
          <IonCol>
            <IonCard button>
              <IonImg src = "dunno"></IonImg>
              <IonCardHeader>Club Name</IonCardHeader>
              <IonCardContent>Quick description of the club</IonCardContent>
            </IonCard>
          </IonCol>
        </IonGrid>
      </IonContent>
    </IonPage>
  );
};

export default Tab2;
